          you can compare before and after.
        </p>

        <h3>Why Convert HEIC to JPG, PNG, or WebP?</h3>
        <p>
          Apple introduced <strong>HEIC</strong> (High Efficiency Image Container) as the default photo
          format starting with iOS 11 in 2017. While HEIC offers excellent compression — photos are about
          half the size of JPEGs at the same visual quality — the format has significant compatibility
          limitations:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Windows:</strong> Cannot open HEIC photos without a paid ($0.99) HEVC codec extension from the Microsoft Store.</li>
          <li><strong>Android:</strong> Most Android devices cannot open HEIC files natively. Some newer Samsung and Google Pixel devices support it, but compatibility is inconsistent.</li>
          <li><strong>Web browsers:</strong> Only Safari supports HEIC in the browser. Chrome has limited support on macOS and Android. Firefox does not support HEIC at all.</li>
          <li><strong>Email and messaging:</strong> Most email clients and messaging apps (Gmail, Outlook, WhatsApp, Telegram) cannot display HEIC images inline. They either fail to load or appear as unopenable attachments.</li>
          <li><strong>Social media:</strong> Facebook, Twitter/X, Instagram, LinkedIn, and most other platforms require JPEG or PNG uploads. HEIC files will be rejected or automatically converted (often with quality loss).</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Supported HEIC Conversion Options</h3>
        <p>ToolBox Image HEIC Converter supports three output formats to match your specific needs:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>HEIC to JPG:</strong> The most compatible option. JPEG is supported everywhere — every device, every operating system, every website, every app. Best for sharing photos, email attachments, and social media uploads. The quality slider lets you balance file size and image quality.</li>
          <li><strong>HEIC to PNG:</strong> Lossless format that preserves full image quality. PNG files are larger than JPEGs but maintain every pixel of detail. Best for screenshots, graphics, and images that require transparency or further editing.</li>
          <li><strong>HEIC to WebP:</strong> Google's modern image format that offers superior compression. WebP files are typically 25-35% smaller than JPEGs at equivalent quality. Best for web use where you want the smallest possible file size with good quality.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Why Use ToolBox Image HEIC Converter?</h3>
        <p>
          Most online HEIC converters upload your photos to a server, exposing your private images.
          ToolBox Image HEIC Converter is different:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>100% Private:</strong> No uploads, no servers, no tracking. All HEIC decoding happens in your browser using a WebAssembly build of libheif.</li>
          <li><strong>No File Size Limits:</strong> Convert HEIC photos of any size — the only limit is your device's available memory.</li>
          <li><strong>No Sign-Up:</strong> Start converting immediately. No account creation, no email, no credit card required.</li>
          <li><strong>Quality Control:</strong> Fine-tune output quality with a precise slider (1-100%) to balance file size and image clarity.</li>
          <li><strong>Instant Preview:</strong> See your original HEIC photo and converted output side by side with exact file size information.</li>
          <li><strong>Free Forever:</strong> Unlimited conversions, no watermarks, no paywalls, no hidden charges.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>How to Convert HEIC to JPG Online</h3>
        <p>Converting HEIC photos with ToolBox Image is simple and takes just a few seconds:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Upload your HEIC photo</strong> — Click the upload area or drag and drop an HEIC/HEIF file from your iPhone, iPad, or any device using Apple's HEIC format.</li>
          <li><strong>Choose output format</strong> — Select JPEG for maximum compatibility, PNG for lossless quality, or WebP for the smallest file size.</li>
          <li><strong>Adjust quality</strong> — Move the quality slider to control the output file size. Higher values (92-100%) produce better quality images. Lower values (60-80%) create smaller files ideal for the web.</li>
          <li><strong>Preview the result</strong> — See your original HEIC photo and the converted image side by side with file size details. The HEIC decoder processes everything in your browser using WebAssembly.</li>
          <li><strong>Download</strong> — Click the download button to save your converted image. Your original HEIC file is never uploaded or modified — all processing stays on your device.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Common Use Cases</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Convert HEIC to JPG for Windows:</strong> Transfer photos from your iPhone to a Windows PC and convert them to JPEG so you can view, edit, and share them without installing additional codecs.</li>
          <li><strong>Convert HEIC to JPG for email:</strong> Most email clients cannot display HEIC photos. Convert them to JPEG before attaching to ensure your recipients can view them regardless of their device or operating system.</li>
          <li><strong>Convert HEIC to JPG for social media:</strong> Upload HEIC photos to Facebook, Instagram, Twitter/X, and LinkedIn by converting them to JPEG first. Most platforms strip or reject HEIC files.</li>
          <li><strong>Convert HEIC to JPG for web uploads:</strong> Many websites, forms, and applications only accept JPEG or PNG uploads. Convert HEIC files to compatible formats before submitting.</li>
          <li><strong>Convert HEIC to PNG for editing:</strong> If you need to edit an iPhone photo in software that doesn't support HEIC, convert to lossless PNG first to preserve full image quality during the editing process.</li>
          <li><strong>Batch convert HEIC photos:</strong> After a trip or event, batch-convert all your iPhone HEIC photos to JPEG to create a universally compatible photo album for sharing with family and friends.</li>
        </ul>
